Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.30,0:00:48.92,特效2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,1500)\move(1860,900,1860,1100)}沙漠作业
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.80,0:01:17.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}大家好 欢迎收看《伟大的旅程》\N{\fs100}Hello, and welcome to The Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.88,0:01:21.88,顶端1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}Sterrato在意大利语中指泥土
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.88,0:01:21.88,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这是一辆兰博基尼飓风Sterrato\N{\fs100}and this, the Lamborghini Huracán Sterrato.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:25.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}与普通版不同 这辆车的设计初衷\N{\fs100}Unlike the normal Huracán, which was designed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.56,0:01:29.12,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}不是为了在市中心的深夜里 缓缓驶过招摇过市\N{\fs100}to prowl round city centres late at night doing nine miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.12,0:01:34.00,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}而是旨在以极速横穿沙漠\N{\fs100}this was designed to blast across a desert doing a hundred and sixty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.00,0:01:37.48,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这款车配备了车顶架 轮拱加宽了\N{\fs100}It's got the roof racks, it's got the flared wheel arches,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.48,0:01:40.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}底盘加强了护板 悬挂行程也加长了\N{\fs100}it's got beefed-up undersides, long-travel suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.44,0:01:44.84,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}它就是兰博基尼的痞子英雄\N{\fs100}It is the Lamborghini 'Rogue Hero'.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.56,0:01:48.72,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}进入沙漠拉力细分市场的不是只有兰博\N{\fs100}And it's not just Lamborghini getting in on the desert raid act.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.72,0:01:51.12,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这是保时捷911 Dakar\N{\fs100}This, is the Porsche 911 Dakar.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:55.12,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}搭载四轮驱动 配备车底护板\N{\fs100}It has four-wheel drive, skid plates
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.12,0:01:59.08,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}离地间隙比普通911高出50毫米\N{\fs100}and fifty millimetres more ground clearance than a regular 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.08,0:02:01.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}就连摩根也跃跃欲试\N{\fs100}Even Morgan's having a go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.36,0:02:05.76,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}没错 这是CX-T 同样像是踩在高跷上\N{\fs100}Yup, this is the CXT and it too stands upon stilts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.16,0:02:10.48,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}它配备了可调节的拉力赛规格减震器 以及外部防滚架\N{\fs100}It's got adjustable rally spec dampers and an external roll cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.60,0:02:11.72,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}漂亮\N{\fs100}Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.92,0:02:15.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}毫无疑问 这几款车都出类拔萃\N{\fs100}All these cars are of course very tremendous,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.44,0:02:18.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}但价格也确实不菲\N{\fs100}but they're also very not cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.44,0:02:21.88,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这辆保时捷售价17万3千英镑\N{\fs100}The Porsche is a 173,000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:25.08,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}摩根售价20万4千英镑\N{\fs100}The Morgan is 204,000
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.08,0:02:28.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}而兰博 售价25万英镑\N{\fs100}and this is 250,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.56,0:02:30.04,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这引发了我们的思考\N{\fs100}And that got us thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.60,0:02:33.40,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我们能不能花更少的钱 造出一辆拉力赛车\N{\fs100}Could we build a rally raid car for less?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.28,0:02:36.80,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}少得多\N{\fs100}A lot less.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.28,0:02:45.32,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}好了 来看看我们买到的车\N{\fs100}Let's have a look at what we've bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:47.96,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我选了这辆 玛莎拉蒂GranCabrio\N{\fs100}I went for this, a Maserati GranCabrio,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.96,0:02:51.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}价格略低于2万6千英镑\N{\fs100}for which I paid just under 26,000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:53.24,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}理查德哈蒙德买了这台\N{\fs100}Richard Hammond has bought this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.24,0:02:57.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}阿斯顿马丁DB9 V12 Volante\N{\fs100}it's an Aston Martin DB9 V12 Volante,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:03:00.28,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}价格为2万2千英镑\N{\fs100}which cost him 22,000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:02.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}杰里米克拉克森买了这辆\N{\fs100}And Jeremy Clarkson, this,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.44,0:03:07.28,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}捷豹F-Type V6S 花了2万5千英镑\N{\fs100}the Jaguar F-Type V6S, 25,000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:12.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}一猜就是制片人威尔曼先生发来的短信\N{\fs100}And needless to say, we've just had a text from Mr Wilman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.56,0:03:13.76,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}念吧\N{\fs100}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.76,0:03:18.64,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}他说 你们需要把买来的车改装为沙漠赛车\N{\fs100}It says, "You will now turn your purchases into desert racers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.64,0:03:20.00,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}改装完毕后\N{\fs100}When you finish,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.00,0:03:24.08,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}前往位于毛里塔尼亚的\N{\fs100}you will report to the railway station in the town of Choum,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:26.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}舒姆镇火车站报到\N{\fs100}which is in Mauritania."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.92,0:03:30.72,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-毛里塔尼亚在哪里 -也许他把 毛里求斯 拼错了\N{\fs100}Where's Mauritania? Perhaps he's misspelt Mauritius?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.72,0:03:33.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}哪儿都不是 这是一个虚构的地方\N{\fs100}Well, it isn't anywhere. It's not a real place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:35.96,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-毛里塔尼亚 -你到底是什么意思\N{\fs100}-Well, Mauritania. -What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.96,0:03:37.16,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}拜托\N{\fs100}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.56,0:03:39.52,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}《狮子 女巫与"镜"》\N{\fs100}"The Lion, the Witch, and the Looking Glass,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:41.36,顶端1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}此处哈蒙德将C.S.刘易斯作品中《爱丽丝镜中奇遇》和《纳尼亚传奇》的名字和剧情搞混了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:41.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}《爱丽丝"魔衣橱"奇遇记》\N{\fs100}"Alice Through the Wardrobe," all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:43.32,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}穿过衣橱\N{\fs100}You go through the back of the wardrobe,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:46.04,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}会遇到会说话的狮子\N{\fs100}you say a cheery hello to the talking lion as you pass in,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:49.72,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}以及穿着扑克牌图案背心四处乱跑的人\N{\fs100}and you watch out for the people running about with playing cards on as tabards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.72,0:03:52.48,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}你说的都是C.S.刘易斯著作里的剧情\N{\fs100}You've got C.S. Lewis echoing around in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:53.80,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-没错 -刘易斯卡洛尔\N{\fs100}-Yes. -Lewis Carroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.80,0:03:55.40,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}那些都不是旅行指南\N{\fs100}They were not travel books.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:57.28,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}你觉得这个地方根本不存在吗\N{\fs100}You don't think this place exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.28,0:03:59.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}没有毛里塔尼亚这个地方\N{\fs100}There's no such place as Mauritania!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:05.64,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}然而事实证明哈蒙德说错了\N{\fs100}It turns out, however, there is such a place as Mauritania.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.00,0:04:10.08,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}毛里塔尼亚位于西非 是一个前法国殖民地\N{\fs100}It's a former French colony in West Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.08,0:04:13.52,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}景色是这样的\N{\fs100}And this is what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:23.80,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这个国家的面积比英国大四倍\N{\fs100}Two thirds of this vast country, it's four times bigger than the UK,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:27.60,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}其中三分之二的土地被撒哈拉沙漠所覆盖\N{\fs100}has been buried...by the Sahara Desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:32.24,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这意味着在大多数情况下 沿途都是\N{\fs100}Which means that for the most part, it is mile after mile
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.20,0:04:36.52,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}毫无人烟的空旷之地\N{\fs100}of nothing... and nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.64,0:04:43.68,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}但在这片巨大炙热的\N{\fs100}But here, in the middle of this gigantic sea
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.68,0:04:45.92,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}空旷之地的中央\N{\fs100}of super-heated emptiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:49.00,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}确实有一条铁路\N{\fs100}there is a railway line,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.00,0:04:51.80,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这条铁路也确实穿过了\N{\fs100}and it does pass through the small town
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.80,0:04:53.92,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}威尔曼先生让我们汇合的小镇\N{\fs100}we've been told to report to...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.70,0:05:00.50,特效3,,0,0,0,,{\pos(3000,1960)}舒姆 人口2735
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:07.70,特效3,,0,0,0,,{\an6\pos(3400,1800)}温度\N46摄氏度
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:18.08,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我听说毛里塔尼亚的物价很低\N{\fs100}I'm told you get a lot more for your money in Mauritania.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:21.60,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我以为这里动物会说话之类的\N{\fs100}I thought it'd be more colourful, with talking animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.60,0:05:23.12,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这里很漂亮也很安静\N{\fs100}It's nice and quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.72,0:05:24.68,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}是啊\N{\fs100}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.68,0:05:26.32,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}天气太热了 都不好发出声\N{\fs100}It's too hot to make any noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:29.40,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}确实很热 46度\N{\fs100}It's really hot. 46 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:32.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}但这里是干热\N{\fs100}It's a dry heat though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:34.04,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}别说...我讨厌那个词\N{\fs100}Don't say, I hate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.04,0:05:35.88,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}就是单纯的热\N{\fs100}It's just hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:38.20,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-那里有一家餐厅 -哪里\N{\fs100}-Ooh there's a restaurant. -Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:39.92,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}哦对了 我们买不到啤酒\N{\fs100}Let's get a... Oh, we can't get a beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:41.68,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-什么 -这个国家禁酒\N{\fs100}-What? -Dry country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.36,0:05:43.92,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-什么 -毛里塔尼亚禁酒\N{\fs100}-What? -Mauritania's dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:45.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-真的吗 -这是穆斯林国家\N{\fs100}-Seriously? -It's Muslim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:49.28,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}究竟什么样的童话世界 不供应金酒呢\N{\fs100}What kind of fairy-tale land doesn't serve gin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.80,0:05:52.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我倒是带了一些含酒精的洗手液\N{\fs100}I do have some mildly alcoholic hand sanitiser, if that's any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.44,0:05:54.16,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}务必妥善保管\N{\fs100}Keep hold of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.96,0:05:59.84,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我只想说 能够再次拍摄真正意义上的《伟大的旅程》\N{\fs100}Can I just say how nice it is to be back doing The Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:01.00,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-感觉真好 -是啊\N{\fs100}-proper Grand Tour. -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:02.44,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}-你们懂我的意思吗 -懂\N{\fs100}-Know what I mean? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.44,0:06:05.36,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}可以来到这种尘土飞扬的世外国度\N{\fs100}Somewhere dusty and in this case, imaginary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.36,0:06:07.88,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}他是来修理这辆货车的车身吗\N{\fs100}Is this man coming to do some panel beating on this van?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:09.32,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我知道是怎么回事了\N{\fs100}I know what this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:11.60,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}这是一辆货车 是一辆非常破旧的货车\N{\fs100}It's a van. It's a really old broken van.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:13.84,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}我们出发之前 威尔曼先生说过\N{\fs100}Mr Wilman said before we left...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:20.20,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}他说 我提供了一辆备用车 以防你们谁的车出了故障\N{\fs100}He said, "I've provided a backup vehicle for if one of your cars goes wrong."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.20,0:06:22.16,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}他为什么要派一辆货车过来\N{\fs100}Why has he sent a van?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.16,0:06:25.56,字幕1080,,0,0,0,,{\be30}他说我们这次旅途所需的一切\N{\fs100}And he says everything we need for this trip
